58
00:02:50,002 --> 00:02:51,543
you'd probably start with something where

59
00:02:51,543 --> 00:02:54,165
the game gets harder when the player gets

60
00:02:54,165 --> 00:02:54,965
further into the game.

61
00:02:55,699 --> 00:02:57,700
and get a nice upward slope like that.

62
00:02:57,700 --> 00:02:59,681
And if you're a masochist, maybe you're gonna make a game

63
00:02:59,681 --> 00:03:02,142
get immediately hard and then stay just super hard

64
00:03:02,142 --> 00:03:05,983
the whole time, like Super Meat Boy or something like that.

65
00:03:05,983 --> 00:03:09,505
I like this idea of, I call it the heartbeat curve.

66
00:03:09,505 --> 00:03:12,226
So it's a gentle slope, but it has periodic spikes

67
00:03:12,226 --> 00:03:13,887
and dips in it.

68
00:03:13,887 --> 00:03:15,187
We'll zoom in here on that.

69
00:03:16,788 --> 00:03:22,553
And the idea is you start out with and introduce a mechanic and it's a super easy to play level.

70
00:03:22,553 --> 00:03:25,515
The player can't really fail, they just get used to the idea.

71
00:03:25,515 --> 00:03:29,438
Then you start to twist the mechanic and add little changes to it and slightly challenge

72
00:03:29,438 --> 00:03:31,600
the player further along in the levels.

73
00:03:32,009 --> 00:03:34,310
And then finally, there's a big spike in the difficulty.

74
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:35,711
It's not terrible, but it's there.

75
00:03:35,711 --> 00:03:38,672
And the player gets a rush, and then they accomplish,

76
00:03:38,672 --> 00:03:40,372
and they beat the mid-boss or the boss,

77
00:03:40,372 --> 00:03:42,193
and it's a big spike there, and it feels good.

78
00:03:42,193 --> 00:03:44,994
And then you start over, but it dips way down.

79
00:03:44,994 --> 00:03:46,515
So the difference is really sharp,

80
00:03:46,515 --> 00:03:49,436
and the player gets a big, full relief feeling,

81
00:03:49,436 --> 00:03:51,877
and they feel like they really accomplished something cool.

82
00:03:51,877 --> 00:03:53,057
And then you introduce a new mechanic,

83
00:03:53,057 --> 00:03:55,518
and the whole process starts over there.

84
00:03:57,368 --> 00:04:02,110
So that's my heartbeat curve. There's also a really good talk on the GDC Vault for free

85
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:07,452
about the game called Jelly Splash. They have a whole different take on the difficulty curve.

86
00:04:07,452 --> 00:04:12,215
It's a mobile game. It's really popular. It's probably designed to teach you how to

87
00:04:12,215 --> 00:04:16,317
just vacuum cash out of players' wallets. You should go look at it. It's really smart.

88
00:04:17,477 --> 00:04:19,198
So when you're thinking about difficulty curves,

89
00:04:19,198 --> 00:04:21,679
there's the concepts of puzzle difficulty

90
00:04:21,679 --> 00:04:22,960
and skill difficulty.

91
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:26,463
So puzzle difficulty is the idea of how hard is it

92
00:04:26,463 --> 00:04:28,184
for a player to figure out what to do,

93
00:04:28,184 --> 00:04:30,586
and the skill difficulty is how hard is it

94
00:04:30,586 --> 00:04:32,507
for them to execute it with their hands in the controls.

95
00:04:32,507 --> 00:04:35,349
You could actually probably plot both these two

96
00:04:35,349 --> 00:04:37,330
on two different types of difficulty curves for your game.

